The paper presents a new algorithm for online linear regression for learning compact reinforcement-learning representations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper explores applications of the algorithm in learning reward functions and probabilities of action outcomes in various RL settings, indicating that it may also belong to the Robotics (cs.RO) and Systems and Control (cs.SY) sub-categories. Finally, the paper discusses the complexity bounds of the algorithm, suggesting that it may also belong to the Data Structures and Algorithms (cs.DS) sub-category.
